exive Pragmatik leiten zum positionierten Hinschauen und Sehenlernen an und binden selbst das Publikum in eine forschende Rezeption ein.  afunded by SFB 1187 Medien der Kooperation (Universität Siegen)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aVisual anthropology. 4aBeobachtung. 4aCultural Studies. 4aDokumentarfilm. 4aFilm. 4aLaborstudien. 4aMedienethnographie. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aNonverbale Praktiken. 4aPerformative Ethnographie. 4aPragmatik. 4aPraxeologie. 4aQualitative Sozialforschung. 4aReflexive Methodologie. 4aVisuelle Anthropologie. 4aWittgenstein. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aDocumentary Film.  aFilm.  aMedia Ethnographic.  aMedia Studies.  aNonverbal Practices.  aObservation.  aPragmatics.  aPraxeology.  aQualitative Social Research.  aReflexive Methodology.  aVisual Anthropology.  aWittgenstein.2 aSFB 1187 Medien der Kooperation (Universität Siegen)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2023z9783111024950oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839435311?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839435311zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839435311/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSLb2023  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-TGPb2023